{{Quote|I wasn't all that fond of the way that the previous books had gone. I hated what the male writers had done to Leia (making her a wife and mommy instead of the strong woman that she was), and so I just went back to the first three films, which I really, really loved. I worked as well as I could within the framework of the previous novels, ignoring as much of them as possible, and restoring as much of what I loved about ''Star Wars'' as possible. Lucasfilm was very supportive. They gave me pages of detailed notes when I was done, but those were mostly terminology nits, not actual changes.|Kristine Kathryn Rusch|<ref name="Interview">{{WebCite|url=https://starwarsinterviews.com/various/authors/kristine-kathryn-rusch-author|text=Kristine Kathryn Rusch (Author)|author=[[Dennis Pellegrom]]|date=2018-11|work=[[Star Wars Interviews]]|archivedate=20230205201523|nolive=1}}</ref>}}
'''Kristine Kathryn Rusch''' is the author of ''[[The New Rebellion]]'' and the ''[[Diplomatic Corps Entrance Exam]]'', and also participated in ''Star Wars on Trial''.

